<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900403-0070</DOCNO><DOCID>900403-0070.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Zurn Industries Inc.:   Power Equipment Company   Wins $66 Million in Pacts</HL><DATE>04/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ZRN CGP</CO><LP>   Zurn Industries Inc. said it was awarded two contractstotaling $66 million to design and build combined cyclecogeneration power plants.   The Erie, Pa., power equipment maker said one is from amember of Sithe/Energies Group of New York to build a56-megawatt plant in Sherill, N.Y. The plant is scheduled tobegin operations by October 1991. Electricity from the plantis to be sold to Niagara Mohawk Power Corp. Steam from theplant will be used by Oneida Silverware Co., Zurn said.</LP><TEXT>   The second order is for a 50-megawatt plant for CoastalPower Product Co. at Fulton, N.Y. Coastal is a unit ofCoastal Corp., a Houston energy concern. The plant, which isset to begin commercial operation in May 1991, will provideelectricity to Niagara Mohawk Power Corp. and will sell steamto Nestle Foods Corp., Zurn said.</TEXT></DOC>